Recording.Name: Validate updating existing Vendor record On-hold functionality with reason code set to - Invoice and still allows for a PO to be created for that vendor

Node.Description: Go to Procurement and sourcing > Vendors > All vendors.
In the list, click the link in the selected row.
On the Action Pane, click Vendor.
Click Edit.
In the Street field, type a value.
In the Name or description field, type a value.
Click OK.
Use the shortcut for switching to View or Edit mode.
Select No in the Report 1099 field.
Click Save.
Click On hold to open the drop dialog.
In the Vendor hold field, select an option.
Click OK.
Close the page.
Go to Procurement and sourcing > Purchase orders > All purchase orders.
Click New.
In the Vendor account field, enter or select a value.
In the list, click the link in the selected row.
Click OK.
In the list, mark the selected row.
In the Item number field, enter or select a value.
In the list, select row 2.
In the list, click the link in the selected row.
Click Save.

RootScope.Name: Validate updating existing Vendor record On-hold functionality with reason code set to - Invoice and still allows for a PO to be created for that vendor
